2 tablespoon Garlic Herb Butter
1 unit Mini Cucumber
¼ ounce Dill
1.5 tablespoon Sour Cream
1.5 ounce Greek Vinaigrette
10 unit Falafel
2 unit Whole Wheat Pitas
5 ounce Baby Spinach
4 ounce Grape Tomatoes
½ cup Feta Cheese
4 tablespoon Roasted Red Pepper Hummus
½ ounce Sliced Almonds
1 teaspoon Cooking Oil

• Drop garlic herb butter
(in packet) into a glass of warm
water to soften. Wash and dry
produce.
• Thinly slice cucumber. Chop
dill fronds.
• In a bowl, mix sour cream
and vinaigrette.

• Drizzle oil in a hot pan. Cook
falafel until golden and crispy,
2-3 minutes per side.
• Toast pitas. Spread with garlic
herb butter. Cut into wedges.

• Toss spinach with creamy
dressing.
• Top spinach with cucumber,
dill, falafel, tomatoes, feta,
hummus, and almonds. Serve
with garlicky pita.